The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama on the anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA). The proclamation highlights the importance of the ADA in ensuring equal rights for individuals with disabilities and acknowledges the contributions they have made to society. It also emphasizes the need to continue working towards full inclusion and equal opportunities for people with disabilities. The proclamation mentions various initiatives and reforms implemented by the Obama administration to support individuals with disabilities, such as expanded funding for education, healthcare reforms, and programs to assist with independent living. The proclamation also encourages Americans to visit Disability.gov for resources and information related to disabilities. Lastly, it mentions the United States signing the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities, emphasizing the importance of advancing disability rights globally.